Tributes continue to pour in for poet and anti-apartheid activist, Don Mattera. Mattera was buried last night according to Muslim rites in Lenasia. Historian Pitika Ntuli discussed this with eNCA's Tumelo Mothotoane. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A man who loved his land and especially his children is how poet and anti-apartheid activist Don Mattera is being described. He died on Monday aged 87. Historian Pitika Ntuli has described Mattera as a true Africanist. WATCH: Don Mattera remembered "My memory of him is that he was a compassionate man, very committed, really loved his people and land but mostly his children," Ntuli said. "Despite what apartheid system did, he was house arrested and he came out defiant. "I remember one of his poems after his house arrest " where was I...." very politically committed, a true Africanist. He was that kind of a person."